A Brief History of the Gamertag

Back when Xbox Live launched in 2002, the idea of having a unified online name was revolutionary. No more "Player1" nonsense. You had a gamertag—and it was yours.

Over time, as the player base exploded, so did the demand for unique names. That's why Microsoft moved from the original one-name-per-world model to the current suffix system.

